Title: Self-consistent determination of hard modes in hot QCD
Authors: A. Ni\'{e}gawa
Comments: 32pages, Figures are not included
Report-no: OCU-PHYS 162
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D55 (1997) 4997-5014; Erratum-ibid. D56 (1997) 2475
\\
  We determine self-consistently the hard-quark and hard-gluon modes in hot
QCD. The damping-rate part in resummed hard-quark or hard-gluon propagators,
rather than the thermal-mass part, plays the dominant role.
